rate of change of speed per unit time

Ball P has velocity \(1.30 \text{m s}^{-1}\) to the right. Ball Q has velocity \(0.50 \text{m s}^{-1}\) to the left

the point beyond which Hooke's law is not obeyed
the point beyond which the wire cannot return to its original length
the point beyond which the wire starts to deform plastically

16 cm
17 cm
33 cm

a decreased wavelength of the sound waves

sound waves
